{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to build and run the Swift Package Registry Service."}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Getting started","modules":[{"name":"App"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/App\/documentation\/App"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Github-Personal-Access-Token","text":"Github Personal Access Token","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Many methods of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/rest?apiVersion=2022-11-28","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is accessible without authentication."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/rest\/using-the-rest-api\/rate-limits-for-the-rest-api?apiVersion=2022-11-28"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are much lower. Therefore, it is advisable to provide the service with a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.github.com\/en\/authentication\/keeping-your-account-and-data-secure\/managing-your-personal-access-tokens","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to authenticate with the Github API."}]},{"text":"Building and running migrations","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Building-and-running-migrations"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Check out the repo and do an initial build using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" command line:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["git clone https:\/\/github.com\/CrowdStrike\/swift-package-registry-service.git","cd swift-package-registry-service","swift build"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now let’s set up the database which is used for parts of the disk cache:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["swift run App migrate"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You should see something like:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["$ swift run App migrate","...","Build of product 'App' complete! (92.19s)","Migrate Command: Prepare","The following migration(s) will be prepared:","+ App.CreateRepositories on <default>","Would you like to continue?","y\/n> "],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type ‘y’ and then hit Return. Then you should see:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["y\/n> y ","[ INFO ] [Migrator] Starting prepare [database-id: sqlite, migration: App.CreateRepositories]","[ INFO ] [Migrator] Finished prepare [database-id: sqlite, migration: App.CreateRepositories]","Migration successful"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now you should see a directory created called ","type":"text"},{"code":".sprsCache","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"db.sqlite"},{"type":"text","text":" file inside that directory:"}]},{"code":["$ ls -l .sprsCache","total 48","-rw-r--r--  1 <your-username>  staff  24576 Mar 24 14:27 db.sqlite"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"text":"Running the service from the command line","level":2,"anchor":"Running-the-service-from-the-command-line","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that you have created the disk cache database, then you are now ready to run the service:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["$ export GITHUB_API_TOKEN=\"<your-Github-PAT>\"","$ swift run App serve","Building for debugging...","...","Build of product 'App' complete! (25.07s)","[ NOTICE ] Server started on http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Testing the service using curl","anchor":"Testing-the-service-using-curl"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before you point Swift Package Manager at this service, you might want to do some simple curl’s to see it run.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"All of the examples below use "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as an example."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The sections below give examples of each of the 5 endpoints of the service."}]},{"anchor":"List-Package-Releases-using-curl","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"List Package Releases using curl"},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["$ curl --no-progress-meter -H \"Accept: application\/vnd.swift.registry.v1+json\" http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture","{","  \"releases\" : {","    \"0.1.0\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.1.0\"","    },","    \"0.2.0\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.2.0\"","    },","    \"0.3.0\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.3.0\"","    },","    \"0.3.1\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.3.1\"","    },","    \"0.4.0\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.4.0\"","    },","    \"0.5.0\" : {","      \"url\" : \"http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.5.0\"","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Fetch release metadata using curl","level":3,"anchor":"Fetch-release-metadata-using-curl"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["$ curl --no-progress-meter -H \"Accept: application\/vnd.swift.registry.v1+json\" http:\/\/127.0.0.1:8080\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\/0.5.0","{","  \"id\" : \"pointfreeco.swift-overture\",","  \"metadata\" : {","    \"repositoryURLs\" : [","      \"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture\",","      \"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-overture.git\",","   